      "note_no": "4712",
      "note": "From degrading servitude, Israel was delivered, and taken, in spite of many rebellions and backslidings on the way, to \"a land flowing with milk and honey\", where later they established the glorious kingdom of David and Solomon. This was not merely fortuitous. In Allah's prescience it was to be a link in furthering the great universal Plan. But their being chosen did not mean that they could do what they liked. In that sense there is no \"chosen race\" before Allah. But Allah gives every race and every individual a chance, and when the race or individual fails to live up to it, he or it must fall and give place to others."
